---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import TextTransformer from '@/components/TextTransformer';
---

<MainLayout 
  title="UwU Translator" 
  description="Convert your text into cute UwU speak with our free online UwU translator"
>
  <TextTransformer 
    client:load
    title="UwU Translator" 
    description="Transform your text into adorable UwU language" 
    transformType="uwu"
    placeholder="Enter your text to make it uwu-fy..."
  />

  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
      <div class="p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">About UwU Translator</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
          <p>The UwU Translator converts regular text into the adorable "UwU speak" that's popular in internet culture, anime communities, and among furries. It makes your text sound cute and playful!</p>
          <p>UwU speak involves replacing certain letters and adding cute expressions to make text sound more kawaii (cute). It's a fun way to express yourself online!</p>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-2">How to Use</h3>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>Enter your normal text in the input box</li>
            <li>Watch it transform into cute UwU speak</li>
            <li>Copy the UwU-ified text</li>
            <li>Share your kawaii message with friends</li>
          </ol>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-2">UwU Transformations</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>Replaces "r" and "l" with "w" (hewwo instead of hello)</li>
            <li>Changes "n" + vowel to "ny" + vowel (nyan instead of nan)</li>
            <li>Adds cute emoticons like uwu, owo, >w<, ^w^</li>
            <li>Makes "th" sounds into "d" sounds</li>
            <li>Converts text to lowercase for extra cuteness</li>
          </ul>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-2">Perfect for</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>Anime and manga communities</li>
            <li>Gaming chats and Discord servers</li>
            <li>Social media posts for extra cuteness</li>
            <li>Roleplaying and character interactions</li>
            <li>Adding kawaii flair to messages</li>
            <li>Making friends smile with cute text</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">Remember: UwU speak is meant to be fun and cute! Use it with friends who appreciate this style of communication. UwU! (◡ ω ◡)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
